All,<br><br>
There is an old saying that ignorance is bliss.<br><br>
Lets ignore the &quot;shrink4u&quot; stuff.<br><br>
I know it is fun sparring, but like the ducks in the carnival shooting range, &quot;shrink4u&quot; just keeps popping up again for more abuse. Actually, I was thinking more of the green plastic silhouette targets on the M16 range in basic training.<br><br>
The funny thing about &quot;shrink4u&quot; is that he really fretters away time that all of us could put to better use. He can only define himself in a world he can control. Because he can't control things here, it drives him crazy, and he just keeps at it. Another funny thing is that no matter what anyone says or does, or what evidence is presented that shows contradictory and/or unacceptable behavior, &quot;shrink4u&quot; just ignores it and keeps chugging along with the same worn out rhetoric. It is getting so predictable in all its forms, it is actually becomming boring!<br><br>
As I posted elsewhere, this type of behavior can be characteristic of people missing big important chunks of their mind. I do not know if this is really the case with &quot;shrink4u&quot;, because someone may be paying him to act this way, too. Cash for crap! Isn't that a curious thought! However deeply we delve into motive for all of this, we keep comming up empty. The problem is that our selection criteria is probably alltogether too normal.<br><br>
Just remember, it wasn't too long ago that some of the &quot;shrink4u&quot; trade kept ice picks in their pockets for lobotomies on the fly. Sound familiar here? <br><br>
So, what more can I say?<br><br>
Bored with Bedlam<br><br>
(Wasn't Bedlam an old English shrink house?)<br><br>
Five days till the full moon!<br><br>
  
